<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>All of our extension inherit on one way or another from Base.php which has a single __toString() method defined as:</p>

<pre><code>public function __toString()
{
    return $this-&gt;getText();
}
</code></pre>

<p>It would be nice if all of the extensions implemented this better so that you can do what you can currently do with YouTube/Extension/Statistics.php:</p>

<p>$s = new Zend_Gdata_YouTube_Extension_Statistics(1, 2,3, 4,5);
echo $s . "\n";</p>

<h1>outputs:</h1>

<p>View Count=1 VideoWatchCount=2 SubscriberCount=3 LastWebAccess=4 FavoriteCount=5</p>

<p>Definition:</p>

<pre><code>public function __toString()
{
    return 'View Count=' . $this-&gt;_viewCount .
        ' VideoWatchCount=' . $this-&gt;_videoWatchCount .
        ' SubscriberCount=' . $this-&gt;_subscriberCount .
        ' LastWebAccess=' . $this-&gt;_lastWebAccess .
        ' FavoriteCount=' . $this-&gt;_favoriteCount;
}
</code></pre>

